## Stack
- WordPress classic theme (no block editor, no FSE, no theme.json)
- Custom Post Types (CPT) registered via functions.php
- No Gutenberg blocks — use Classic Editor

## WordPress rules
- Register CPTs in functions.php using register_post_type()
- Use template hierarchy for CPT templates (single-{post-type}.php, archive-{post-type}.php)
- Enqueue scripts and styles properly via wp_enqueue_scripts hook
- No page builders — custom page templates only
- Custom meta boxes for CPT fields (see Meta boxes section)
- Keep functions.php organised with clear sections (CPTs, enqueues, hooks, helpers)
- Use get_template_part() for reusable template chunks
- child theme safe — no direct parent theme edits

## Meta boxes
- No plugins for custom fields — write meta boxes from scratch
- Register meta boxes using add_meta_box()
- Save with sanitize_text_field() / wp_kses_post() depending on field type
- Use nonce verification on every meta box save
- Store with update_post_meta() / get_post_meta()
- Group related fields into one meta box where it makes sense
- No ACF, no Pods, no Toolset
